Incident Description: LINUX_sun - ibclogec2.ib : Swap area occupied 93.35%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
Resolution Description: Issue: Swap memory was almost full on client node Ibclogec1.ib. Later, we received alerts for swap memory memory on second client node. Analysis: Elasticsearch client nodes having a light memory leak and after running for 1 or 2 months, they start consuming swap space quickly. Hence it is required to restart ES services the client nodes in every approx 2 months. Business Impact: If a client node leaves the cluster than it would impact kibana visualization and users will not be able to make requests through kibana. Resolution: Restarted elastic search services on client node Ibclogec1.ib and than on client node (Ibclogec2.ib)

Incident Description: INCIDENCIA NETTING - RE: FACTURA MELIA COMPENSACIÓN - RITM0830575
Resolution Description: Hi Team, We’ve been reviewing the invoices and if you realize the total amount is 0, because in AP we have +30.250 and in AR -30.250, so it supposes that it’s balanced. Anyway, we’ve been looking for information in Oracle Standard Support about this issue and we have found the following information: “No transactions were selected for netting since there were no outstanding balances in AP and AR. Hence, No transaction has been selected for related supplier/ supplier site and related customer / customer site hence, validation failed. Please check the outstanding balance. If there is no outstanding, there is no need for the Netting batch.” So, if there is no outstanding amount it won’t be created, are you sure that aren’t there more transactions? Because if we have one transaction in AP and one transaction in AR with the same amount it won’t be created..
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

Incident Description: Escalado Job: Mail message from CONTROL-M: Ha fallado el job A18OJB04 en zlc , avisar en horario la
Resolution Description: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso A18OJB04. Impact: Medio, el proceso es un previo al DATAB EV que si no se ejecuta no se puede ejecutar los procesos del DATAB EV. Root Cause: La suma de distancias ortodromicas de los tramos es cero. En el fichero EA18.TRASDES.V1712 existen tramos en el que el campo DEDFDIST ( distancia ortodromica) esta a cero. Steps Taken: Búsqueda de la procedencia del la suma de distancias ortodromicas. Correción del fichero EA18.TRASDES.V1712 para los tramos afectados con la distancia correspondiente. Relanzar el proceso desde el principio. Termina OK.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

PNRs: Q58OFL y TDNNY5 1/18/2018 4:29:56 PM, NIIT.averma, We have requested digital business some information: " Hi Digital Support Team, We have looked into the document and this is not helping us as this was prepared four years back in 2014 and as you are also aware that things are changing daily on the platform. So we would request some information from based on which we can only proceed further in this case. Please provide the below information : 1. Is this the only case or there are such other cases as well ? If yes please provide few more cases to get a better view of the issue ? 2. Is this the only scenario (2 ADT + 1 INF) where this issue is occurring ? Please have some test with other combinations as well like below and share the results: a. 1 ADT + 1 INF b. 1 ADT + 2 INF c. 3 ADT + 1 INF d. 2 ADT + 2INF The above information is important to know because it may be possible that this scenario haven´t been take into account while the functionality was developed or may be it is a future enhancement. We will proceed with further investigation only after your valuable inputs in the above context. " [2018/01/17] LEDA.lnavio: reasignamos con funcional antiguo, no encontramos nada más reciente, de todas formas esto ya ha pasado alguna vez más. No encontramos referencia. 1/17/2018 8:14:06 PM, NIIT.averma, Received the information regarding the code: This development was developed by Indra. However, the authorization and payment distribution I'm sure that it's done in Class ConfirmOnHoldAction.java. Search HBFF mark or comment in the code of this class. Investigating further. attached is the email for detailed information. 1/10/2018 3:10:15 PM, NIIT.averma, Hi Team, Please check this incident and suggest. The 3EUR have been discount for each passenger (2ADT+1INF) so the total discount was 9EUR instead of 10EUR of the On-Hold fee payed by the customer. I seems that the problem is related to the infant that there aren´t on-hold fee for this kind of passenger but when is going for ticketing the infant is take as other passenger so the total On-Hold fee is share through the 3 passengers, so 10/3=3.33333 but only write 3 EUR without decimals in the FP, here is the problem. Probably this scenario haven´t been take into account in. Please check about this point and confirm this, maybe have to be a future enhancement. Regards, Anurag 1/9/2018 8:37:51 PM, NIIT.averma, We have checked the logs and the On-Hold amount of 10 EUR is already paid by the user. When user went to pay for the rest of 213.27 EUR then the payment was authorized but there was an error in the online emission so the tickets were generated offline : In FP there are multiple payment method this is why 3 EUR are shown. We are checking that what are these 3 EUR there in the FP.

Incident Description: ING011- 07/01/2018 - un proceso de PROS OD que se ejecuta todos los domingos se ha creado bloqueado
Escalado Job: Mail message from CONTROL-M: Ha fallado el job A18OJB10 en zlc , avisar en horario la
Resolution Description: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso A18OJB10. Impact: Medio, el proceso es un previo al DATAB EV que si no se ejecuta no se puede ejecutar los procesos del DATAB EV. Root Cause: La suma de distancias ortodromicas de los tramos es cero. En el fichero EA18.TRASDES.V1712 existen tramos en el que el campo DEDFDIST ( distancia ortodromica) esta a cero. Steps Taken: Búsqueda de la procedencia del la suma de distancias ortodromicas. Correción del fichero EA18.TRASDES.V1712 para los tramos afectados con la distancia correspondiente. Relanzar el proceso desde el principio. Termina OK.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

Action taken : Checked and found schedulers were expired. extended their date of ending in BBDD. Monitored the functionality for few days and found working fine. 1/15/2018 4:09:13 PM, NIIT.skumar3, We have checked and monitored the mails sent during last 2-3 days and functionality is working fine as usual, please refer mail attached We are proceeding to update incident as resolved as no further action required. 1/12/2018 7:59:40 PM, NIIT.skumar3, I have updated the value ‘SCHEDULED_END_DATE ‘ to ‘31/12/2019’ in table IB_PE_LOAD_SCHEDULES only and further checking other tables if any other having same situation. We will check tomorrow if the problem resolved by this update or not. [2018/01/09] LEDA.mclemente: Subimos la prioridad porque siguen llegando e-mails a los mismos con los que se ha reportado la incidencia.

Incident Description: Caida capacidad por falta de vuelos
Resolution Description: el problema viene dado porque la captura de datos que se lanza a las 20:00, coincidió con el proceso de actualización de inventario (Schedule). El Schedule no suele correr a esas horas, pero a causa de una carga de vuelos masiva que se había enviado ese día y previendo que podía causar problemas durante el proceso nocturno, se lanzó más tarde de lo previsto, solapándose con el proceso de captura de datos. Para que un vuelo se envíe a Pros tiene que estar consolidado en el inventario, los vuelos indicados fueron procesados con posterioridad a las 20:00 por lo que no fueron enviados en ese fichero pero sí en el siguiente

Resolution Description: Issue: Application Iberia Agencies giving error intermittently Analysis: We checked the log files and found fatal errors related to weblogic server. Resource limit exception was found in logs that indicated the the number of resources available in the server are not enough to handle the incoming requests Impact: Downtime of Iberia Agencies application causes revenue loss to Iberia as the agencies are not able to make group bookings and refund requests Resolution: Due to the ongoing campaigns in Iberia, the traffic was high and the application was not able to withstand the situation. We worked with DBA and Weblogic team and increased the maximum connection limit from 25 to 35 in weblogic server, which resolved the issue --------------------------------------------------------------- Duplicate of INC00000097247 and we are monitoring it.. ------------------- Got confirmation from Tomas that Iberiagencias is working fine now. However, we are still monitoring the application and request business to let us know in case of any issue. Incident Description: [PORTAL EMPLEADO] Aparecen varios avisos y mensajes que no puede cerrar.
LINUX_sun - wlcarga1.ib : Pool JDBC IAGCargo3^IAGCargo3^IAGCARGOWSR+bdlcarga-scan+IBSISCAR no Activo
LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 91.64%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
Resolution Description: Issue: Swap memory almost full on client node Ibclogec1.ib Analysis: As elastic search services as build on Java. There is always some memory leak on the client nodes as a result after sometime the swap memory starts to be build up on client nodes. Business Impact: In case swap memory is almost full the client node may leave the ELK cluster and will not be able to take requests from Kibana. Resolution: Restarted elastic search services on client node Ibclogec1.ib.

Por favor cambie la fecha de planificación de la revisión a la fecha de ejecución del trabajo actual y publíquela nuevamente desde AMOS. Déjenos saber si necesita alguna otra ayuda de nuestra parte

1/25/2018 7:06:47 PM, NIIT.prani, Issue Description : Payment refused in Mexico Market Business impact : It has an impact on payments of MX market. Action taken : As issue has resolved long back and temporary solution has been provided for alert part, we are resolving this incident. We are working on the permanent solution for alert and chasing for RCA with netplus team paralally. Relevant mails are attached for the reference. Issue: ERROR: “Error bancario. El banco devuelve un mensaje que no se puede procesar”.was occurring in Mexican market since January 04,2018 (however reported on 9th Jan) and it was happening on the NETPLUS payment gateway with Visa and Master Card so was raised to Netplus on 9th. An estimated 23% transactions were impacted. Resolution: Netplus have confirmed that they are not seeing the error any more from Evalon post 10 Jan 2018 19:51:32. Yesterday, Service got deactivated as the no. of errors were high. However, no alert was triggered (we are checking the reason why, as alerts for other markets are being received). As a workaround, below mentioned changes were made in the HOT table for service continuation yesterday and will continue this until the alert is in place and confirmation receive from all parties that MX payments are stable. • Threshold limit has increased to six times. • Auto activation switch has been enabled. • Time window for Auto-activation is kept to 30 Minutes. • We will also keep a watch over the service in HOT table manually over different intervals. [1/19/2018 ] NIIT.abansal, Netplus has not confirmed yet about RCA of the issue, mail sent yesterday,a awaiting response. 1/9/2018 5:40:17 PM, NIIT.prani, We have sent the below to netplus. Mail is attached for the reference. "We have the following error in the payment in the Mexican market; rejection message “Error bancario. El banco devuelve un mensaje que no se puede procesar”.This error has started to occur on January 4,2018. It is happening on the NETPLUS payment gateway with Visa and Master Card. Please have a look. Impact: 20 PNRs of average per day."

Incident Description: Fallo Software: PAGINA WEB DE IBERIAGENCIAS NO FUNCIONA
Resolution Description: Issue: Application Iberia Agencies giving error intermittently Analysis: We checked the log files and found fatal errors related to weblogic server. Resource limit exception was found in logs that indicated the the number of resources available in the server are not enough to handle the incoming requests Impact: Downtime of Iberia Agencies application causes revenue loss to Iberia as the agencies are not able to make group bookings and refund requests Resolution: Due to the ongoing campaigns in Iberia, the traffic was high and the application was not able to withstand the situation. We worked with DBA and Weblogic team and increased the maximum connection limit from 25 to 35 in weblogic server, which resolved the issue --------------------------------------------------------------- Duplicate of INC00000097247 and we are monitoring it.. ------------------- Got confirmation from Tomas that Iberiagencias is working fine now. However, we are still monitoring the application and request business to let us know in case of any issue. Incident Description: LINUX_ibm - El job: F86O03 con OrderID: 2xkh4 del DataCenter: CTM_SERVER en la maquina: zlc, Aplicac
Resolution Description: Pendiente subida a producción día 22 del programa F86T331 Issue: Falla el proceso porque el programa va a buscar en la DGIMCA el código numerico de la moneda y no encuentra la moneda SDP. Impact: Bajo. Root Cause: La moneda SDP es un caso especial en el que tiene un nombre distinto en los dos campos afabeticos de la tabla (MCACALF y MCACALFV) Steps Taken: Se modifica el programa F86T331 para que busque el código numero en ambos campos alfabeticos. Se relanza el proceso y finaliza correctemewnte.

PNR: QHV39Z In this case the 3DS available was sent as YES, which we have seen in our logs as well. PNR: POZ6HJ In this case the user has tried four times and each time the card was rejected. First three time user has used the VISA CREDIT,BANK OF AMERICA - CONSUMER CREDIT and each time the 3DS available was sent as YES and fourth time user has used AMERICAN EXPRESS CREDIT,AMERICAN EXPRESS US CONSUMER and this time it was sent as NO. Since both these cases are the wrong ones, we have asked digital business on the below queries as it will help to find out the cause faster: - What are the ideal working scenarios ? - What was reflected in CYB in the first three transactions of PNR POZ6HJ ? - What should be the actual configurations ? Attached is the email sent to digital support team. 1/22/18 5:17:06 PM, NIIT.RGAUTAM, We have investigated and didn’t found any relevant data regarding the PNR UDTV69 provided as example in the incident. We cannot see the FP and other details. Since this PNR is showing cancelled BY START OVER in the Amadeus logs . Please provide more examples so we can understand the flow better and proceed to our investigation. Mail Attached.

Incident Description: Clientes que no reciben ofertas ni promociones
Resolution Description: Issue : User was not able to receive offers and promotions from Salesforce Marketing Cloud. Analysis : we analyse that the user should not present in any of the Auto Suppression List if he wants to receive offers and promotions from Salesforce Marketing Cloud, we checked there and user was not present in any of the Auto Suppression List. Also he must be present in LK_CLIENTE_OBJECTIVO, we checked there and user was also present there. Impact : As the user was nreceive offers and promotions from Salesforce Marketing Cloud he might miss important offers and promotions and can escalate iberia for that. Resolution : we checked in Auto Suppression List by raising case to Salesforce and user was not present in any of the Auto Suppression List. So we asked customer to send us the failed email or JOB ID so that we can investigate further on it, but customer was unable to send us the JOB ID even after 3-4 chasers. Once the customer will receive the JOB ID they will raise a new Incident.

Incident Description: SIC011: Incidencia sobre algoritmo de Forward Revenue
Resolution Description: He ejecutado la consulta en varias ocasiones y no consigo que me devuelva el error. ¿Siempre se usan los mismos filtros? Creo que el problema puede venir por el comportamiento de OBIEE al exportar a texto plano. En la consulta que me mandas el total de filas gira en torno a las 9000 sin embargo al exportar se acerca más a las 11000. Esto se debe a que en el texto plano se muestran los datos sin agrupaciones, una fila devuelta por la base de datos por una en el fichero, además de hacer de nuevo la consulta a la base de datos para traer los registros en detalle. Si alguna de las consultas es distinta puede acercarse al límite de filas exportables o tiempo de permanencia de la query en la base de datos.

Resolution Description: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso I19O046. Impact: Se retrasa la carga de la información que contiene el fichero. Root Cause: El sistema de recepción de ficheros, cuando el fichero es muy grande, cataloga el fichero antes de que esté completamente transmitido y lanza el proceso finalizando con error porque el fichero recibido no esta completo. Incident Description: Escalado Job: Mail message from CONTROL-M: Ha fallado el job I19O047 en zlc , avisar en horario lab
Resolution Description: Issue: Falla el proceso porque un fichero que nos envían de fuera ha llegado sin registro de pie. Impact: Se retrasa la carga de la información que contiene el fichero. Root Cause: El sistema de recepción de ficheros, cuando el fichero es muy grande, cataloga el fichero antes de que esté completamente transmitido y lanza el proceso finalizando con error al faltar parte del fichero. Steps Taken: Se localiza el fichero completo entre los recibidos en cmem y se fuerza su paso a las carpetas de /datos para que así se cargue y ejecute así el proceso de nuevo.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

El error viene por el agente que introduzco la tarjeta en el sistema, el cual puso la credit card con 16 dígitos. BAP 1,CC1766640999461022,0122 Evidentemente para nosotros es imposible saber qué dígito es el que puso de más, El número de token se genera a partir de la credit card introducida, si se introduce mal, el token se generará mal, con los mismos digitos que la tarjeta. 1000001771271022 Por nuestra parte no podemos decirdir si se pasa a perdidas o no. Contactar con el departamento funcional para estas consultas. Help Desk PSS RESTKT <IBPSS.HDRESTKT@iberia.es>; DS/PSS COORD <pss.coord@iberia.es>

Buenos días Javier, Después de revisar este caso vemos que existen 3 movimientos de 775000000 JPY en la cuenta 57348000. A continuación los 3 asientos: COMENTARIOS ACCOUNT CP DB PERIOD NAME CURRENCY CODE ENTERED_DR ENTERED_CR ACCOUNTED_DR ACCOUNTED_CR CURRENCY CONVERSION_DATE CURRENCY CONVERSION_RATE CURRENCY CONVERSION_TYPE DESCRIPTION DESCRIPTOR PERIODO PRESUPUESTARIO CENTRO_DE TESORERIA PAIS JOURNAL_NAME BATCH_NAME JE_HEADER_ID Movimientos de creación del cobro IB66893 57348000 CP69001A 101 07-17 JPY 775000000 6235882,5 31/07/2017 1 User 75554 00000IB66893 07-17 CG000100 JAPÓN 31-JUL-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 637020 16742987 1999844 57700308 CP09082A 101 07-17 JPY 775000000 6235882,5 31/07/2017 1 User 75554 CP09082A2807 07-17 CP69001A JAPÓN 31-JUL-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 637020 16742987 1999844 Movimientos de reversión del cobro IB66893 57348000 CP69001A 101 08-17 JPY 775000000 6235882,5 04/08/2017 1 User 75554 00000IB66893 07-17 CG000100 JAPÓN 04-AGO-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 642001 16774315 2002122 57700308 CP09082A 101 08-17 JPY 775000000 6235882,5 04/08/2017 1 User 75554 CP09082A2807 07-17 CP69001A JAPÓN 04-AGO-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 642001 16774315 2002122 Otro cobro que tiene el mismo código IB66893 57348000 CP69001A 101 08-17 JPY 775000000 5989963,38 31/08/2017 1 User 77910 00000IB66893 07-17 CG000100 JAPÓN 31-AGO-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 644006 16810507 2003320 57700302 CP09064A 101 08-17 JPY 775000000 5989963,38 31/08/2017 1 User 77910 CP09064A2807 07-17 CP69001A JAPÓN 31-AGO-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 644006 16810507 2003320 Como se observa, el tipo de cambio es 1 y el tipo es “Usuario”. Esto ocurre cuando en la importación del asiento en GL, el importe en moneda local viene ya informado (no se calcula con el tipo de cambio), por lo que en este caso la fecha del tipo de cambio informada en GL no es la real. El tipo de cambio real de los cobros se aplica en el módulo de Contabilidad Auxiliar (SLA) cuando se contabiliza el cobro y vuelca a GL tal cual (Copy-Paste). La fecha del tipo de cambio es 31/07/2017 y viene así desde el cobro y su reversión, aunque esté posteada la reversión en agosto, el tipo de cambio de la reversión es de julio. Cualquier cosa que necesite, no dude en comentárnoslo. Gracias. Un cordial saludo. Soporte Sistemas Financieros.

Incident Description: LINUX_sun - ibclogec2.ib : Swap area occupied 93.74%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGro
Resolution Description: Issue: ELK- swap memory was almost full on the ibclogec2.ib client node Analysis: Elasticsearch client nodes having a light memory leak and after running for 1 or 2 months, they start consuming swap space quickly. Hence swap memory was almost full on one of the client node. Business Impact: We need to get the client node into elastic search cluster as soon as possible as it can effect the request and response from the Kibana and users might have problem is searching logs & indices in Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on ibclogec2.ib client node and it rejoined the ELK cluster.

Incident Description: Escalado Job: LINUX_ibm - El job: X25OBIM2 con OrderID: 2y12v del DataCenter: CTM_SERVER en la maqu
Resolution Description: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso X25OBIM2 porque no ha ejecutado el proceso X25OLST del que controla la condición. Impact: Medio, al no ejecutarse el X25OLST se retrasa la entrega del fichero IB-MERGER-LOADSTATS al proceso que lo explota y por tanto el producto final. Root Cause: El X25OLST no se ejecuto porque el proceso X25OI21 no tenia activiada la condicion FICI281-OK 1601. Steps Taken: Añadir la condicion FICI281-OK 1601 para que se ejecute el proceso X25OI21 y se ejecute el proceso X25OLST. Una vez ejecutado el X25OLST se borra el X25OBIM2 fallado.

Issue: In Semi-automatic notifications" that are dated January 11th , although user have "Rejected" them every day, they go out again by email. Impact: User was getting email alerts again and again for semi-automatic notification for same rejected flight. Analysis: As per analysis in lower environment there are many tables are impacted (dependant) by rejecting flight list. As per business logic user has to choose the reject cause option from the menu(Sin motive IB8xxx). After that related data will be update and delete from the tables e.g. ibc_notifications,ibc_semiaut_notif_pending,IBC_GROUPS_TAB,ibc_failed_notifications. Resolution: After some time user has confirmed by email, that the issue has been fixed.

Incident Description: Fallo Peoplesoft: Incidencia PeopleSoft Informe de cupos

Resolution Description: ISSUE: Execution of the PATROCINADOS process failed with below error for 15th Jan 2018; ALERTA-ERROR-PROCESO:AGREGA_PATROCINADOS IMPACT: If the files are not loaded then the BI reports will not show correct data and the aggregation based on it will be calculated incorrect. ANALYSIS: There is a record in WEB_LOG_CAMPANAS whose length is 161 and thereby failing as the column length of COD_CRM in WEB_LOG_CAMPANAS_AG is 140. RESOLUTION: , this data is generated from the ib.com portal and after the scripts are executed tables are loaded successfully these files are not kept as backup because of their size.These are the bad records which are discarded due to the datatype mismatch .We don’t need to reprocess it again.

Resolution Description: Se modifican algunas consultas del objeto etl y se aumenta el rendimiento.

Issue: The scheduled job failed as the previous day load was still running. Impact : Minimum impact as the data window is 'sysdate -3 ' so there is no data loss. Analysis: The job on 17th Jan 2018 was in running state because of which the next scheduled job (18th Jan 2018 &19th jan 2018) failed.This job took more than 60 hours and still did not finish. This job has a data windoe of 'sysdate -3 ' so the job can be killed and can be rerun. Resolution: The running job's session was killed and the sceduled job for the next executed .The load was successful.

Resolution Description: Issue: Falla el proceso porque un fichero que nos envian de fuera ha llegado sin registro de pie. Impact: Se retrasa la carga de la información que contiene el fichero. Root Cause: El sistema de recepción de ficheros, cuando el fichero es muy grande, cataloga el fichero antes de que esté completamente transmitido y lanza el proceso finalizando con error al faltar parte del fichero. Steps Taken: Se revisa que el fichero ya lo tenemos completo, y se ha ejecutado otro proceso posterior correctamente, por lo que se borra el proceso fallado.

Incident Description: Fallo Software: Sin acceso a Interline

Resolution Description: Grupo AM: 1. Analizar el PNR fallido => No tiene los elementos de la historia para extraer la fecha de creación => Se opta por procesar el fichero con P (no cargar este PNR, no es la primera vez que se recibe por lo que ya está cargado en los sistemas) 2. LINUX (odtx): Eliminar el flag de error 3. LINUX (odtx): Comprobar que no se está ejecutando el proceso de JBGROUP que podría provocar error al usar el mismo proceso. 4. LINUX (odtx): Generar el fichero PNRLoader a partir del GRPFILE existente: 5. Esperar correo con NOCRI , que no exista errores tanto para GRPFILE como PNRLOADER 6. LINUX: Verificar en la ruta pros/GRMS_DATA/input, el fichero IB.PNR.fecha_fallida.X_1.xml 7. LINUX (odtx): Mover el fichero SCORT a su ubicación correcta 8. Esperar que este fichero se cargue junto con el de esta noche.

Resolution Description: Issue: Error in GREX dataware house daily load. Analysis: GREX daily load failed as the 21st Jan 2018 files were received late from the Source team 'NIIT_MTO_GESING'. Business Impact: Users will not be able to see data in OBI reports for the missing dates. It will impact the reports users are making in order to take decisions based on group bookings. Resolution: There was an issue with source team system due to which there was delay in the daily files. Once we received the files from the source team, we reprocessed the daily load in ODI load plan: LP_GREXDWH_CARGA_DAILY and checked logs for successful execution of the reports.

Resolution Description: Issue: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors. Impact: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: "####<ene 25, 2018 3:27:37 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl1.ib> <Aeropuertos1> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1516890457104> <BEA-310002> <59% of the total memory in the server is free> ####<ene 25, 2018 3:24:07 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1516890247981> <BEA-310002> <72% of the total memory in the server is free> " Their was a CRQ (CRQ000000107127) implementation by DBA's to increase the pool size today which may be the reason for this issue. The CRQ was successfully implemented by the DBA's. Resolution: Since the errors stopped appearing in the log and there is no memory issue, so we are closing this INC.

Resolution Description: Issue: El proceso I32OAJBI5 ha fallado por la clase de cabina errónea. Impact: Baja, no se genera el fichero de obtención IB+ para DATA B. Incident Description: LINUX_sun - apliwebl2.ib : Pool JDBC Aeropuertos2^Aeropuertos2^IBCONECTPRO+bdl+ibutf8 no Activo. Avi
Resolution Description: Issue: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors. Impact: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned weblogic logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: "####<ene 25, 2018 3:27:37 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl1.ib> <Aeropuertos1> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1516890457104> <BEA-310002> <59% of the total memory in the server is free> ####<ene 25, 2018 3:24:07 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1516890247981> <BEA-310002> <72% of the total memory in the server is free> " Their was a CRQ (CRQ000000107127) implementation by DBA's to increase the pool size today which may be the reason for this issue. The CRQ was successfully implemented by the DBA's. Resolution: Since the errors stopped appearing in the log and there is no memory issue, so we are closing this INC.
Se comprueba acceso tras desbloqueo.

Issue: During the archival process of old snapshot backup 'backup-2017.12.04', the snapshot was not deleted from the snapshot repository of NFS_backup drive. Analysis: We checked in the logs and found that that backup was archived however the step of deletion of backup from the snapshot repository did not takes place. Business Impact: High disk usage in NFS_backup drive can prevent future snapshots to be created. And ELK cluster can become unstable if backup policies don't work well. Resolution: We checked with the Linux team if the archival of backup.2017.12.04 is present. After confirmation , we deleted this snapshot from the NFS_DRIVE

Incident Description: [IMM003] EC-MBU ERROR TRANSFER TALLY B S8075316
LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI?N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM
Resolution Description: <ISSUE>:: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors.The logs genarted by Ibconecta showed that there were connectivity errors. <IMPACT>:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database and hence no new notifications from IbConecta <ANALYSIS>:: As per the support document incident we request DBA team to check the errors, we check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors but more often than not the connectivity is restored itself. <STEPS TAKEN TO RESOLVE>:: As said, we moitored the database for a while and the connectivity was restored. We checked in the logs to verify the connection. <PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? (Yes, No).>:: NO <CAN THIS INCIDENT BE PREVENTED? (Yes, No)> :: No, Its an intermittent issue, when the databse connectivity is lost and Ibconnecta keeps polling for the connection.We had also asked DBS to increase the Pool size which might prevent this issue.

Incident Description: Incidencia RES: ResIber no respondiendo a Sabre/AA en cascading
Resolution Description: Hi, Flight IB3876/AA8727 wasn’t properly loaded on the system, so PNR creation messages were rejected to an internal queue when related with this flight. That is the reason why you don’t receive an ACK response message with Resiber PNR. When the message is treated the flight sell is rejected with NO action code. I copy you the sequence that happened to a test PNR that you created: The message from the 22nd of January is rejected to a queue: ILLEGAL ACTION LINE 6 <QP: QK MADRMIB .HDQRMAA 222030 RQR HDQAA DQEFES/BB7B/99999999/DFW/1S/T/US 1SINGH/BUTCH TEST IB6166Q/AA8640Q18APR BOSMAD CS1/1725 0620/1 IB3876Q/AA8727Q19APR MADSCQ CS1/0725 0840 Is reprocessed manually: HDQRMAA .MADRIIB 241444 HDQAA DQEFES/BB7B/99999999/DFW/1S/T/US MADIB P6PPE 1SINGH/BUTCH TEST IB6166Q/AA8640Q18APR BOSMAD CH1 IB3876Q/AA8727Q19APR MADSCQ NO1 SSR OTHS IB KK/ CODESHARE FLIGHT OR CLASS INVALID Now, the flight is properly loaded on the system. Please, try to do a new reservation on that flight to see if everything is working properly. Thanks&Regards.

Incident Description: OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT
Resolution Description: Issue: Error encountered during execution of IB Card Assignment out File. Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds data of the Card Assignment points, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Avios points against their Iberia Cards. Analysis: File arrived late hence the load plan failed.Therefore manually re ran the load plan to successfully send the IB Card Assignment file to IB Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for IB Card Assignment file to successfully process the load.

Resolution Description: Issue: Oracle BI Publisher Notification: [Boris report Weekly new]: Job was failed. Business Impact: User's are not able to recieve the schedule report having the claims data. Analysis: The “Boris” Report job has failed on 15/01/2018. We have analyzed that the issue is with the 09/01/2018 data. There is a record against 9th Jan 2018 where the Customer Name field is having special character in it due to which the report is failing due to “Rendering Document” error. Resolution: The special character needs to be removed from the field value from the source.

Resolution: We changed the time stamp of delayed file and manually ran the automation for that file and it ran successfully.

Incident Description: Escalado Job: Mail message from CONTROL-M: Ha fallado el job I32O000 en zlc , avisar en horario lab
Resolution Description: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso I32O000. Impact: Medio, no se procesa el fichero de carga de pasaje y PFS para la aplicación I32. Root Cause: En la rutina I32RMIL2 accede a la tabla BEACU.TACUFMI con la cia del acuerdo y la clase equivalente para recuperar el factor millas clase. El proceso falla porque existen duplicados en el factor millas clase. Steps Taken: Solicitud para eliminar de la tabla BEACU.TACUFMI el factor millas clase duplicados. Recibido el aviso de que se dio de alta el factor de millas clase. Relanzar el proceso desde el paso fallado. Termina OK.
